{"parse":{"title":"Johnston light machine gun","pageid":44249247,"revid":795154478,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em;width:25.5em;border-spacing:2px;\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"hproduct\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background-color:#C3D6EF;text-align:center;vertical-align:middle;font-size:110%;\"><span class=\"fn org\"> Johnston D1918 LMG </span></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;text-align:center;border-bottom:1px solid #aaa;line-height:1.5em;\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_1.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Johnston Model D1918 machine gun 1.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3c/Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_1.jpg/300px-Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_1.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"233\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3c/Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_1.jpg/450px-Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_1.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3c/Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_1.jpg/600px-Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_1.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3229\" data-file-height=\"2504\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:1em\">Type</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Light_machine_gun\" title=\"Light machine gun\">Light machine gun</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:1em\">Place&#160;of&#160;origin</th><td>\nUnited States</td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#C3D6EF;text-align:center;vertical-align:middle;font-size:110%;\">Specifications</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:1em\"><a href=\"/wiki/Cartridge_(firearms)\" title=\"Cartridge (firearms)\">Cartridge</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/.30-06_Springfield\" title=\".30-06 Springfield\">.30-06 Springfield</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:1em\"><a href=\"/wiki/Action_(firearms)\" title=\"Action (firearms)\">Action</a></th><td>\ngas-operated</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:1em\">Feed&#160;system</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Double_drum_magazine\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Double drum magazine\">double drum magazine</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b> Johnston Model D1918</b> was a <a href=\"/wiki/Light_machine_gun\" title=\"Light machine gun\">light machine gun</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Forgotten,_D1918_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Forgotten,_D1918-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> It is a rare and little-known weapon with scant information available on it. It is best known for its resemblance to the <a href=\"/wiki/Lewis_Gun\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lewis Gun\">Lewis Gun</a>, having a similar <a href=\"/wiki/Gas-operated_action\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gas-operated action\">gas-operated action</a> and a barrel surrounded by a cooling shroud.\n</p><p>The weapon was chambered for the <a href=\"/wiki/.30-06_Springfield\" title=\".30-06 Springfield\">.30-06</a> round, fed from <a href=\"/wiki/Double_drum_magazine\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Double drum magazine\">double drum magazines</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;note 1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The action was gas-operated, with the piston working in a cylinder beneath and integral with the barrel. The Johnston did not use the Lewis's prominent clock spring. <a href=\"/wiki/Cocking_handle\" title=\"Cocking handle\">Cocking</a> of the piece was unusual, the entire pistol grip sliding forwards to engage the action, then returning backwards to cock it.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;note 2&#93;</a></sup> This was first unlocked by a trigger-like mechanism in a cutout through the grip, behind the firing trigger.\n</p><p>The cooling shroud could be removed without tools by unscrewing the front retaining ring from the barrel by hand. The aluminium cooling fins inside were in two pieces and once the shroud was removed, came loose from the barrel. A cold barrel could be unscrewed for field exchange.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;note 3&#93;</a></sup> An integral <a href=\"/wiki/Bipod\" title=\"Bipod\">bipod</a> was attached to the shroud.\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tleft\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_3.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ad/Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_3.jpg/220px-Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_3.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"171\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ad/Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_3.jpg/330px-Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_3.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ad/Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_3.jpg/440px-Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_3.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3229\" data-file-height=\"2504\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_3.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Stripped to major groups</div></div></div>\n<div style=\"clear:both;\"></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Variants\">Variants</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Johnston_light_machine_gun&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Variants\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_2.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/23/Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_2.jpg/220px-Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_2.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"171\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/23/Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_2.jpg/330px-Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_2.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/23/Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_2.jpg/440px-Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_2.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3229\" data-file-height=\"2504\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun_2.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Variant without thermal jacket</div></div></div>\n<p>A variant was produced without the heat shield jacket and with a bare, unfinned barrel. A muzzle counterweight maintained the normal balance position. A further wooden handgrip was provided ahead of the receiver, as the bare barrel would be too hot to hold, unlike the cooling shroud.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Johnston_light_machine_gun&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table role=\"presentation\" class=\"mbox-small plainlinks sistersitebox\" style=\"background-color:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;color:#000\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td class=\"mbox-image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"40\" class=\"noviewer\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/45px-Commons-logo.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/59px-Commons-logo.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1024\" data-file-height=\"1376\" /></td>\n<td class=\"mbox-text plainlist\">Wikimedia Commons has media related to <i><b><a href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:Johnston_Model_D1918_machine_gun\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"commons:Category:Johnston Model D1918 machine gun\">Johnston Model D1918 machine gun</a></b></i>.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: lower-roman;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Rather than the Lewis <a href=\"/wiki/Pan_magazine\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pan magazine\">pan magazine</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">A similar cocking action was used in the Czech <a href=\"/wiki/Besa_machine_gun#15_mm_BESA\" title=\"Besa machine gun\">BESA 15mm</a> and was copied for later models of the <a href=\"/wiki/Besal\" title=\"Besal\">Besal</a> emergency production LMG based on the <a href=\"/wiki/Bren_LMG\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bren LMG\">Bren</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Unlike the Bren, where a side handle with extra insulation and leverage was provided to allow a hot barrel to be changed.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Forgotten,_D1918-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Forgotten,_D1918_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.forgottenweapons.com/light-machine-guns/johnston-model-d1918-machine-gun/\">\"Johnston Model D1918\"</a>. <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.forgottenweapons.com\">forgottenweapons.com</a></i>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=%5Bhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.forgott